<title>AUSTRALIA: RTRS-Ross says to raise A$16.5 million.</title>
<headline>RTRS-Ross says to raise A$16.5 million.</headline>
<dateline>SYDNEY 1996-03-24</dateline>
<text>
<p>Ross Mining NL, which plans to develop a gold mine in the Solomon Islands, said on Monday it will seek to raise A$16.5 million through a placement of 15.75 million shares at A$1.05 each.</p>
<p>Ross said it is looking to raise the funds to ensure the schedule for development of its Gold Ridge mine is not delayed due to outstanding litigation involving some landowners near the mine.</p>
<p>Part of the capital requirements for the mine include a US$23.6 million eight-year limited recourse loan from the Commonwealth Development Corp (CDC).</p>
